  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "I was talking to @vjeux about whether or not `unstable_renderSubtreeIntoContainer` will remain around, and he pointed me to the new/upcoming [`unstable_createPortal`](https://github.com/facebook/react/blob/7d2be2c9a7b4a976e20d2d7c312b43b1bee01a07/src/renderers/dom/fiber/ReactDOMFiber.js#L212) API. I've been using the former to render subtrees that I can move into Atom panes and panels (since I control the node I'm rendering the subtree into, I can move it around as I see fit).\r\n\r\nSo my two questions are:\r\n\r\n1. Will I continue to be able to move this DOM node wherever I want it? (E.g. not just attached to the document like most people do for modals)\r\n2. Will this continue to retain context into the subtree?",
